1
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,867
<i> Based on the CCTV footage,</i>

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,100
<i>Reign was transferred
to another plane.</i>

3
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> And wherever that plane lands,</i>

4
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:18,467
<i>Lieutenant Conde and I
will go there.</i>

5
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> Chief is expediting our visas.</i>

6
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:21,833
<i> Why? Where are we going?</i>

7
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:23,333
<i> We're flying to Dubai.</i>

8
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:25,500
<i>Welcome to Dubai,
Conde and Enriquez.</i>

9
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>He's my batchmate,
Captain Pong Marasigan.</i>

10
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:29,300
<i> Bok, I need your help.</i>

11
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>Boss, I really don't know
anything.</i>

12
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> Do you know anything or not?</i>

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,167
<i> Yes. I'm going to speak now.</i>

14
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,600
<i>We're near the building
my contact mentioned.</i>

15
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,367
<i>Enriquez, come with me,
let's go at the front.</i>

16
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:40,867
<i>- Conde, you cover the back.
- Hey!</i>

17
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,233
<i>- You're not allowed here.
- Who are you?</i>

18
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:46,767
<i> Hey!</i>

19
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:49,800
<i> Markus, we're under attack!</i>

20
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:50,900
<i> Get the girls now!</i>

21
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:55,067
<i>- Please, don't!
- Stop him! Let's go!</i>

22
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,867
<i> Please have mercy! Please!</i>

23
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,633
<i>- Get inside!
- Let me go!</i>

24
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,533
<i>- Selena!
- Sir Tonyo?</i>

25
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:03,733
<i> Faster! Let's go!</i>

26
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,267
<i> Where are the girls?</i>

27
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,600
<i> Where are the girls?</i>

28
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:14,200
They're being taken to the car!

29
00:01:15,767 --> 00:01:16,967
You animal!

30
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:18,500
I even spoke to you in English
because we're in Dubai,

31
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:20,267
but you know how to speak
Tagalog!

32
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:24,867
Sir...

33
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,133
Let's go!

34
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,033
Sir...

35
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:05,833
Stop! Where are we going?

36
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,300
Stop!

37
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,500
Here!

38
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,433
Hurry!

39
00:02:22,567 --> 00:02:25,100
Sir, let's chase them!

40
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,100
- Let's go!
- Okay, Sir!

41
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:55,200
Sir, we need to find a shortcut!

42
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,800
- Here.
- Let's go!

43
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:01,100
Pong!

44
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:02,233
Tonyo!

45
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:14,900
You don't want to fight with me,
okay?

46
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:17,733
Stop, or else you're going
to get hurt.

47
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,500
Tonyo! Tonyo!

48
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:33,933
Pong, the key, hurry!

49
00:03:34,067 --> 00:03:35,467
Let's go!

50
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,267
Sir, here, Sir!

51
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,367
- Sorry!
- Oh!

52
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,833
- Hey! Hey!
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.

53
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:18,867
What is this?

54
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,367
Come on, you have to pay
for that, Bro.

55
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:21,967
Bro, no, no, hey!

56
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,300
You have to pay for that.

57
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:25,600
No, don't touch her!

58
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:26,767
Who's going to pay

59
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:27,967
- for these mandarins?
- We're going to pay later!

60
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:30,433
- You're going to pay this now.
- Yes, we'll pay later!

61
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:31,567
Who's going to pay?

62
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,067
You have to pay.

63
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,167
Sorry, I'll pay later.

64
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,900
- We'll be back! We'll be back!
- We need the money now!

65
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:40,500
Please give me the money now...

66
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:44,467
We just, we just want...

67
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,600
- I don't want to fight.
- We just want the money.

68
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:14,233
- Let's go!
- Sir!

69
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,833
Too bad!

70
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:25,867
We didn't catch them.

71
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:31,067
- Hello, Conde?
- Hello, Sir?

72
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,567
We couldn't catch up
with Bobby's godsister.

73
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,733
<i>How about you guys?
What's the status with Selena?</i>

74
00:05:38,667 --> 00:05:40,900
Yes, Sir, we're following
their van now.

75
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:43,200
Tonyo, it looks like,

76
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:45,667
they're going straight
to the dock.

77
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:52,200
It looks like they're taking
Selena to the yacht, Sir.

78
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:55,067
Okay, we'll follow you there.

79
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,100
Okay, Sir, see you there.

80
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:02,200
Enriquez, the fight
isn't over yet.

81
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,533
If we ever see Selena,

82
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:08,767
maybe we can get information
on how to save Reign.

83
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,267
- Let's go, let's follow Tonyo.
- Thank you, Sir.

84
00:06:46,067 --> 00:06:47,833
Take her in there.

85
00:06:49,433 --> 00:06:50,133
No, don't! Don't!

86
00:06:50,267 --> 00:06:51,167
Inside.

87
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:20,867
It hurts! Stop!

88
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,267
Stop! Let me go!

89
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,733
Set me free!

90
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:24,967
Take her inside!

91
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:27,267
Wait! What do you want from me?

92
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,433
What do you want from me?

93
00:07:28,567 --> 00:07:30,633
Let me go!

94
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:33,233
Stop it! Please!

95
00:07:36,467 --> 00:07:38,633
I thought this was already sold?

96
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:41,367
Police from the Philippines
are chasing after her.

97
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,467
So she's going with us to Milan?

98
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:47,167
Yes, because Markus will meet
someone in Duomo.

99
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,167
That's why she will come with us
to Milan.

100
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,867
You monsters! Bring me back
to the Philippines!

101
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,500
You monsters...

102
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:59,867
Let me go!

103
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
You've been causing trouble
for some time now!

104
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:04,200
You, you behave!

105
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,400
Don't make any trouble.

106
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:22,567
The incident at the safehouse
didn't help.

107
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:24,400
The more you've been implicated,
Sir.

108
00:08:24,533 --> 00:08:25,633
Do you believe

109
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:29,267
that I'm innocent of the charges
against me, Attorney?

110
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,667
Of course.

111
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,867
I'm your lawyer.

112
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,567
I'll always be on your side.

113
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:36,867
But if you're not my lawyer,
what do you think?

114
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,533
Well...

115
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:41,067
to be honest, Sir...

116
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,500
you look really guilty.

117
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:44,633
Then you're fired.

118
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:45,567
Excuse me?

119
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:48,100
Did you hear what I said?

120
00:08:48,233 --> 00:08:50,267
The lawyer I want,

121
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:54,033
is someone who won't question
my innocence,

122
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,567
because that's the truth.

123
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,333
You can leave now.

124
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:09,767
Did you know that the police
officers who confronted us

125
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:13,167
at Selena's safehouse followed
us here in Dubai?

126
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,767
What?

127
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:20,533
Oh, wait, did they get Selena?

128
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:24,567
No, we're on our way to Milan.

129
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,767
Find a way to fix this, Roman.

130
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:29,533
Okay, update me.

131
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:31,667
But make sure that...

132
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,900
that girl doesn't come back
to the Philippines.

133
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,533
No! Let go of me!

134
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:58,433
You all behave, especially you.

135
00:10:24,633 --> 00:10:28,033
Miss, are you okay?

136
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:29,167
What's that?

137
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:30,800
That's a cellphone.

138
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:33,533
How did you get a cellphone?

139
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:34,933
I got it from the guard.

140
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,667
Just don't be so loud, okay?

141
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,700
Miss, do you know
anyone we can call?

142
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,400
Anyone we can ask for help?

143
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,033
Yes, there's someone I know,
a policeman.

144
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:47,200
Sir Tonyo and Ma'am Bobby.

145
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,333
We can ask them for help.

146
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:50,800
Miss, are you from Calabari too?

147
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:51,833
Yes.

148
00:10:51,967 --> 00:10:53,833
Bobby, as in Bobby Enriquez?

149
00:10:53,967 --> 00:10:56,167
Is she the police officer
you're talking about?

150
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,800
- Do you know her too?
- Yes.

151
00:10:57,933 --> 00:10:59,200
Yes, I know Bobby.

152
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,633
She's my godsister.

153
00:11:00,767 --> 00:11:02,333
Okay.

154
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:04,200
Why do you want to call her?

155
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:05,933
Well, she's the only one
I've memorized the number.

156
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:08,967
With Sir Tonyo's, not so much.

157
00:11:09,133 --> 00:11:09,867
They need...

158
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,100
They need to know we're here.

159
00:11:12,233 --> 00:11:14,733
But it seems like
the battery is low.

160
00:11:14,867 --> 00:11:16,567
Go ahead and text Bobby.

161
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,500
Okay, okay.

162
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:20,467
- Watch out, maybe...
- Yes.

163
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:25,200
The phone's dead.

164
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,433
What happened?

165
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:28,633
I think the battery is dead.

166
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:36,567
I'm sorry, Sir.

167
00:11:37,867 --> 00:11:40,867
If only I had caught up
with Selena...

168
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,900
I could have saved them.

169
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:46,500
Don't blame yourself, Conde.

170
00:11:46,633 --> 00:11:48,067
You did everything you can.

171
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,267
Don't worry, Enriquez.

172
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:56,033
Next time, we'll save them both.

173
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,233
As much as I'd like
to join you here,

174
00:11:59,367 --> 00:12:01,500
I have to go home tomorrow

175
00:12:01,633 --> 00:12:04,133
to report to the regional
office.

176
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:08,300
Conde, you'll handle
this mission first.

177
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:10,133
Yes, Sir.

178
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:12,167
Enriquez...

179
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,600
don't be a troublemaker.

180
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:16,367
Yes, Sir.

181
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:20,567
Too bad, if Garcia were here,

182
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,600
I could have asked him
to join you.

183
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:25,800
- Bok...
- Bok!

184
00:12:25,933 --> 00:12:28,400
What are you doing here?

185
00:12:28,533 --> 00:12:29,700
Garcia...

186
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:31,433
are you following us?

187
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:32,933
Are you?

188
00:12:33,067 --> 00:12:35,700
Of course not, Chief,
I'm on vacation mode right now.

189
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:38,233
Here, here's the evidence.

190
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:40,433
I went on a trip.

191
00:12:40,567 --> 00:12:41,900
See, I also went for a stroll.

192
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:46,167
See?

193
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:49,000
If you want, Chief...

194
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:50,133
I'll treat you.

195
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:51,333
My credit card has...

196
00:12:51,467 --> 00:12:52,800
- a big credit limit.
- Garcia!

197
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:54,767
We didn't come here
to have a tour.

198
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:55,667
He's right.

199
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,267
We're here because
we have a mission.

200
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,867
Since you're here already,

201
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,333
can you accompany Conde
and Enriquez?

202
00:13:01,467 --> 00:13:03,267
Because I'm going back
to the Philippines.

203
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,600
Well, Sir, I'm sorry.

204
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:09,167
I'm on vacation mode right now.

205
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:12,000
I want to give in
to your request, but I can't.

206
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,767
I understand, Garcia.

207
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,500
I really can't not follow
your order.

208
00:13:16,633 --> 00:13:17,967
Of course, you're my boss.

209
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:19,567
And what about these two?

210
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:21,667
I'm the best among
the three of us.

211
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:25,167
Bok, this officer of yours
is really different, isn't he?

212
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:30,267
Sir, Selena sent a message.

213
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,333
What did she say?

214
00:13:31,467 --> 00:13:34,400
Ma'am Bobby, this is Selena.

215
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:37,367
Your godsister is with me.

216
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:40,367
I heard from one
of the syndicates...

217
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:44,167
that they'll bring us to Milan,
to Duomo.

218
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:46,700
Sir...

219
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:50,467
Sir, let's go there.

220
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:54,633
Conde, Garcia, and Enriquez...

221
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:57,533
get Selena and the others back.

222
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:59,500
Go to Milan.

223
00:14:00,867 --> 00:14:02,133
Yes, Sir!

224
00:14:02,267 --> 00:14:04,533
Good morning!

225
00:14:04,667 --> 00:14:06,200
Croissant for breakfast!

226
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:08,133
Cold cuts!

227
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:10,233
Spaghetti!

228
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:12,600
Oman Air!

229
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,233
How's Godfather Victor
doing in jail?

230
00:14:16,367 --> 00:14:17,667
He'll rot in there, Boss.

231
00:14:19,933 --> 00:14:22,533
Your father will definitely
win the election.

232
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,267
Does that mean...

233
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,533
we won't have any more problems
with Selena?

234
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,500
Most likely,
Sonny passed on to her,

235
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:37,667
what we're looking for
to pin me down.

236
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,333
Selena doesn't seem to know
anything, Boss.

237
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:42,300
The police didn't get
anything either.

238
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,133
And get her out of your mind,
Sir.

239
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:46,300
First of all,

240
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:47,933
Selena is already in the custody
of our people abroad.

241
00:14:48,067 --> 00:14:50,533
Ready to be sold
to the highest bidder.

242
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:52,067
You don't have a headache
anymore,

243
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,967
and you'll even earn.

244
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,900
I'm on my way.

245
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:33,033
Get ready.

246
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:34,933
Later, we'll go to the event.

247
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:38,300
Just follow
all the instructions.

248
00:15:38,433 --> 00:15:42,300
When they tell you
to stand in the middle, stand.

249
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:46,033
No one should cause trouble
so that no one gets hurt.

250
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:48,233
Especially you,

251
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:49,467
since you're a pain in the ass.

252
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:55,100
Later, I'll make sure
I get rid of you.

253
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:59,200
You, get them ready.

254
00:16:35,033 --> 00:16:36,733
Are you okay, Enriquez?

255
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:41,033
It's beautiful here
in Milan, Sir.

256
00:16:42,733 --> 00:16:45,433
It's just ironic because...

257
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:48,167
this Cathedral is so peaceful,

258
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:50,767
but what we're looking for
are demons.

259
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:55,600
Don't worry.

260
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:58,667
We'll find Reign, Selena,

261
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,233
and the other girls too.

262
00:17:01,367 --> 00:17:02,733
Beautiful!

263
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:09,300
It's beautiful here, Bok! Hey!

264
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,833
Come on, Bok,
let's take a picture!

265
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,533
Bok...

266
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,133
Bok, it's been six hours

267
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:22,467
since Selena last made contact
with us.

268
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,467
Most likely, she's been caught
with a cellphone.

269
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,600
Sir, please.

270
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:30,333
Let's be positive.

271
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:33,133
Okay, Enriquez, I'm positive.

272
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:35,433
I'm positive that Selena
was caught.

273
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:36,400
Bok!

274
00:17:36,533 --> 00:17:37,800
I'm just making
the situation light.

275
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:40,333
Enriquez thinks so negatively.

276
00:17:40,467 --> 00:17:41,733
Think positive.

277
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:44,367
And you're so hot-headed.

278
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,567
You're keeping up
with the heat of Milan.

279
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:48,400
Sir, I need to save Reign.

280
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:51,633
That's why we're going to find
her Filipino handler.

281
00:17:51,767 --> 00:17:55,033
I have a strong feeling
he's just around the corner.

282
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:57,167
So it's better if we...

283
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:59,333
split up.

284
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:01,233
Yes, Sir.

285
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:14,867
Bok, it's so hot here in Milan,
you're still wearing a jacket.

286
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,867
Take that off!

287
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,667
Why? This is the fashion
capital.

288
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,967
It really is hot.

289
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,300
I don't check the weather
forecast.

290
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:22,200
Enriquez!

291
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:24,867
Any news, Sir?

292
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,500
How about you?

293
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,067
Nothing.

294
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:42,700
Do you think they might have
left Milan?

295
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:49,133
The girls are ready.

296
00:22:08,233 --> 00:22:10,300
Bok, any news?

297
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:12,333
Bok, I found him.

298
00:22:12,467 --> 00:22:13,900
You found him?

299
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:15,033
Are you sure?

300
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,533
I'm sure, it's him.

301
00:22:17,667 --> 00:22:19,700
I'll go after him,
I'll send you the location.

302
00:22:19,833 --> 00:22:21,500
Okay, okay.

303
00:22:24,933 --> 00:22:25,967
They are still here.

304
00:23:27,267 --> 00:23:30,000
<i>Forty thousand
for girl number 18!</i>

305
00:23:30,133 --> 00:23:31,667
<i> Going once...</i>

306
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,067
<i> Going twice...</i>

307
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:36,067
<i> Sold to bidder number 14!</i>

308
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:40,400
<i>Girl number 18 is sold
for 40,000 US dollars.</i>

309
00:23:40,533 --> 00:23:42,433
<i>Congratulations,
bidder number 14.</i>

310
00:23:42,567 --> 00:23:44,600
<i> And now, let's bring in...</i>

311
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,300
<i> girl number 19.</i>

312
00:23:51,767 --> 00:23:55,867
<i>Girl number 19,
please come up on stage.</i>

313
00:23:56,033 --> 00:23:59,000
<i>You may scan the QR code,
ladies and gentlemen.</i>

314
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:03,400
<i>Bidding starts
at 30,000 US dollars.</i>

315
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:04,900
30,000, everyone.

316
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:06,167
<i> Okay, bidder number 17!</i>

317
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:07,800
<i> How about 35?</i>

318
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:08,900
<i> Number 8!</i>

319
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:10,167
<i> How about 30? 40?</i>

320
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:12,067
<i> Oh, 40 for bidder number 9.</i>

321
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,933
<i> 45 for bidder number 10.</i>

322
00:24:14,067 --> 00:24:15,933
<i> 75,000!</i>

323
00:24:16,067 --> 00:24:18,767
<i>75,000 US dollars
for bidder number 6!</i>

324
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,033
<i> Any higher than that?</i>

325
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:21,233
<i> Going once...</i>

326
00:24:21,367 --> 00:24:22,833
<i> Going twice...</i>

327
00:24:22,967 --> 00:24:24,900
<i> Sold to bidder number 6!</i>

328
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:29,033
<i>Girl number 19 is sold
for 75,000 US dollars.</i>

329
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,733
<i>Congratulations,
bidder number 6.</i>

330
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:50,833
Roman, these three are really
causing a mess here.

331
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,233
You already know what to do.

332
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,167
Where are you taking
the village chairman?

333
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:57,067
- Mar! Village chairman!
- Village chairman!

334
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:58,467
I am very sorry, Enriquez,

335
00:25:58,600 --> 00:25:59,633
your grandmother
got caught up in this.

336
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:00,867
One hour...

337
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,767
if not, your grandmother's going
to be laid out in a wake.

338
00:26:03,067 --> 00:26:04,167
Enriquez, where are you going?

339
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:05,833
You heard it earlier, right?

340
00:26:05,967 --> 00:26:07,267
So don't stop me!

341
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,133
We need to go to Switzerland.

342
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:10,467
Sir, don't worry.

343
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:12,967
We can use my credit card

344
00:26:13,100 --> 00:26:15,400
because my credit limit's
high anyway.

345
00:26:15,533 --> 00:26:16,933
You can even come along.
